------------------------------------------
DYNAPHOPY 1.0
------------------------------------------
Program to calculate crystal anharmonic frequencies from molecular
dynamics calculation obtained from VASP code.

------------------------------------
Installation instructions
------------------------------------
1. Requisites
Python 2.6 or higher
Matplotlib
Scipy
Phonopy

2. Download the source code a put it in the installation directory

3. Run the setupy script
python setup.py install --home=.

---------------------------------------
Executing the program
---------------------------------------
1) Script method
Create/edit script like input.py and execute it
The comments in the script makes it (hopefully) self explained.

2) Interactive text interface method
Execute text_gui.py and follow the instructions (still under development)

./text_gui.py input_file vasp_MD_OUTCAR

Input files for several compounds can be found in Example directory

